<subSubSection id="B696656AFFEDC618FF6A116F753B9304" pageId="56" pageNumber="2111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FE3336E1FFEDC618FF6A116F753B9304" blockId="56.[92,1047,1359,1543]" pageId="56" pageNumber="2111">
<emphasis id="CCF8EAF3FFEDC618FF6A116F76C99065" box="[132,239,1360,1383]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="2111">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Eyes present. Antennular ¯agellum of three to six articles. Antennal ¯agellum of one or two short articles. Mandibular palp of three articles. Maxillipedal endite small or obsolete; palp of one to two articles, terminal article tiny. Pereopod 1 subchelate, propodus ināted. Pereopods 2 and 3, propodi much less ināted. Pereopods 4±7, carpi roughly rectangular. Pleopod 1, exopod operculiform. Pleonites short, usually free, sometimes fused. Telson lacking statocyst.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
